13/09/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A court in Sarajevo on Friday (September 11th) sentenced former Bosnian Muslim soldier Suad Kapic to 17 years in prison for murdering four Bosnian Serb prisoners of war during the 1992-1995 conflict in the country.
Kapic was found guilty of war crimes, the court said in a statement.
The atrocities happened in the town of Sanski Most in western BiH.
(Hayat, Studio 88, AFP - 11/09/09)
